
http://viveksoni.net/intalling-spring-tool-suites-in-ubuntu/


We are going to install sts in /opt directory


1
cd /opt
 

Step 2:

Now download the tar.gz file you can find new versions from https://spring.io/tools/sts/all


1
wget http://download.springsource.com/release/STS/3.6.3/dist/e4.4/spring-tool-suite-3.6.3.RELEASE-e4.4.1-linux-gtk-x86_64.tar.gz
 

Step 3:

Now extract this tar.gz file


1
sudo tar -xvf spring-tool-suite-3.6.3.RELEASE-e4.4.1-linux-gtk-x86_64.tar.gz
 

Step 4:

Now it will create this directory /opt/sts-bundle/sts-3.6.3.RELEASE so we will create symlink to /opt/sts-bundle/sts-3.6.3.RELEASE/STS in /usr/local/bin/sts


1
ln -s /opt/sts-bundle/sts-3.6.3.RELEASE/STS /usr/local/bin/sts
 

All done you can now run STS by typing “sts” anywhere in shell.
